<item>
            <title>[LU-6054] lustre-initialization-1: mkfs.lustre: FATAL: unhandled fs type 5 &apos;zfs&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6054</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;andreas.dilger@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a7e9eedc-8758-11e4-86dc-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a7e9eedc-8758-11e4-86dc-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test lustre-initialization_1 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;mkfs.lustre: FATAL: unhandled fs type 5 &apos;zfs&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if this is a recent regression of not. I&apos;d been ignoring some of the lustre-initialization-1 failures because I thought they were due to network issues. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: lustre-initialization-1 lustre-initialization_1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
