                            <comment id="103223" author="adilger" created="Mon, 12 Jan 2015 19:04:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7601&quot; title=&quot;lustre-initialization-1: mkfs.lustre: command not found&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7601&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TEI-2163&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102183" author="utopiabound" created="Mon, 22 Dec 2014 16:41:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at ks_post from &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a7e9eedc-8758-11e4-86dc-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a7e9eedc-8758-11e4-86dc-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears that lustre-osd-zfs is not being installed (thus zfs won&apos;t mount or work), maybe this is a TEI issue since root cause seems to be Kickstart not installing needed packages.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102144" author="bfaccini" created="Sat, 20 Dec 2014 13:03:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Humm, I am puzzled here, could this be that review-zfs has recently switched to using DKMS-based RPMs during node-provisioning step ??&lt;br/&gt;
If no network nor installation problem has occured during node-provisioning, this is the only explanation I have for now because due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5851&quot; title=&quot;Handle LU-4606 packaging changes for Lustre Server DKMS RPM&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5851&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5851&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; issue DKMS-based installs are presently broken and should fail the same way.&lt;br/&gt;
Can somebody from the TEI team help in order to describe how node-provisioning works regarding the available RPMs in each build?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102088" author="jlevi" created="Fri, 19 Dec 2014 18:57:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bruno,&lt;br/&gt;
Could you please have a look at this one?&lt;br/&gt;
Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
